item.title: Gunmen Attack Pakistan Stock Exchange, Citing Its Link to China
item.description: Gunmen tried to storm the Pakistan Stock Exchange building in Karachi, but all four died in a shootout with guards without getting inside, police said.

item.title: China Strikes Back at U.S. Move to Restrict Visas for Party Officials Over Hong Kong
item.description: The Chinese government plans to restrict visas for Americans who it deems go too far on matters related to Hong Kong, increasing tensions between the U.S. and China over the territory’s limited autonomy from Beijing.

item.title: India Blocks Chinese Apps, Including TikTok, After Border Clash
item.description: India banned dozens of Chinese mobile apps, including widely used TikTok and WeChat, after a border clash between troops from the two countries left 20 Indian soldiers dead this month.

item.title: Russia Reinforces Foothold in Libya as Militia Leader Retreats
item.description: Moscow is sending reinforcements to Libyan military leader Khalifa Haftar while shopping for new allies in the divided country, as Moscow seeks to shape the fate of the nation and its oil reserves.

item.title: Iran Issues Warrant to Arrest Trump Over Killing of General
item.description: Iran has asked Interpol for assistance in detaining President Trump and 35 others over the killing of Maj. Gen. Qassem Soleimani, who was targeted in an American drone strike in Iraq’s capital in January.

item.title: Brexit Is a Test of De-Globalization in a World of Covid-19
item.description: The impending economic divorce between the U.K. and the European Union has become an experiment in rapid de-globalization against the background of a global pandemic.
